m_q.target_metric: Predict CATEGORY for each ID in test.csv based on text features
filters: test.csv has no CATEGORY column - prediction required
sub_questions: What text features are most predictive of CATEGORY?
How to handle missing or inconsistent publisher/story information?
What is the distribution of categories in training data?
How to preprocess TITLE text for classification?

schema_conflicts: test.csv has 7 columns vs uci-news-aggregator.csv has 8 columns

scale_issues: Text columns (TITLE, URL, PUBLISHER, STORY, HOSTNAME) need normalization
cross_source_conflicts: STORY column appears to be encoded/hashed values - unclear meaning
URLs contain special characters and query parameters

format_notes: STORY column contains alphanumeric codes like 'dQEXtwpswiNW-4MJkBLcTFNZCQ42M'
Titles contain quotes and special characters

constraints: Output file must be named category.csv
Predictions must align with test.csv IDs
Categories likely from set: b, t, e, m (based on training sample)
derived_filters: Handle missing text in TITLE column
statistical_tests: Check for class imbalance in training CATEGORY
Test correlation between PUBLISHER and CATEGORY
output_format_requirements: CSV file with ID and CATEGORY columns
Same row order as test.csv or explicit ID mapping
